It would be extremely convenient if there were a simple way to test whether a set of methods were implemented. I made the title "pseudo-interface" since there is no function overloading in GDScript. Currently you have to for-loop your way through comparisons of the method list and it looks quite ugly when all I really wanna know is whether object X contains a superset of the array of methods I'm passing it.

Bonus points if it could work with either an array of strings OR a Script resource:

    var MyInterfaceMethods = preload("res://MyInterface.gd").get_method_list()
    var hasSubsetOfMethods = true
    for method in MyInterfaceMethods:
        hasSubsetOfMethods &= has_method(method)
    if hasSubsetOfMethods:

becomes equivalent to...

    var MyInterface = preload("res://MyInterface.gd")
    if self implements MyInterface:

or...

    var MyInterfaceMethods = preload('res://MyInterface.gd").get_method_list()
    if self implements MyInterfaceMethods:

